[02_prepare_spatial_rna.py]

Command:
python cell2location_run/scripts/02_prepare_spatial_rna.py

Purpose:
Prepare the spatial RNA matrix as an AnnData object for downstream cell2location analysis.

Input files:
input/GSM6578065_humanskin_RNA.tsv
input/spatial_barcodes_index.txt

Spatial RNA matrix format:
spot x gene

First rows showed:
X      MIR1302.11  RP11.34P13.7  AL627309.1 ...
15x34  1           0             0
34x34  0           1             0
19x30  0           0             0

Original spatial RNA dataframe:
(1691, 15486)

After removing ERCC genes:
(1691, 15471)

Meaning:
1691 spatial spots x 15471 genes

Coordinate matching:
Barcode file spots: 2500
Spatial RNA spots: 1691
Overlap spots: 1691
RNA spots not in barcode file: 0
Barcode spots not in RNA matrix: 809

Interpretation:
The chip contains 2500 theoretical spatial positions.
The RNA matrix contains 1691 expressed or retained spots.
All 1691 RNA spots have matched spatial coordinates.
The remaining 809 barcode positions are likely empty or filtered spots.

